> ## `Git Fork` ##

---

> ![git image](images/Forking.png)

---

### Definition:

"A fork is copy [or a spilt] of a repository that allows
developers to experiment with code and layout changes without
directly impacting the original file verison unless changes are
committed, pushed, and merged.' 
[defintion cited from docs.github.com](https://docs.github.com/en/github/getting-started-with-github/fork-a-repo)

### Additional Resources:
* [How to Fork a Git Repository](https://docs.github.com/en/github/getting-started-with-github/fork-a-repo)
* [Forking Development Projects](https://guides.github.com/activities/forking/)
* [Git Fork vs Git Clone(Paywall)](https://medium.com/@tharis63/git-fork-vs-git-clone-8aad0c0e38c0)